wikipedia_page.main: Elizabeth Mounsey (8 October 1819 – 3 October 1905) was a British organist, guitarist, and composer. She became the organist of St Peter upon Cornhill Church in London when she was 14 years old, and remained in the post until 1882. Mounsey also composed works with her sister Ann Mounsey and Elizabeth had a short career as a guitarist.
